# Product Returns in Circular Supply Chains: Monte Carlo Simulation

This repository contains the full reproducibility package for the manuscript: **"A Monte Carlo Framework for Assessing Economic and Environmental Performance of Product Returns in Circular Supply Chains"**.

## Overview
This simulation evaluates product returns across five circular supply chain sectors using a stochastic Monte Carlo framework. It calculates Total Cost (TC), Return Cost-Performance Index (RCPI), Material Recovery Rate (MRR), Virgin Material Displacement (VMD), and Carbon Equivalent (CO2e) Avoided over 10,000 iterations.

## How to Run the Simulation
1. Clone this repository to your local machine.
2. Install the required dependencies: `pip install -r requirements.txt`
3. Run the main simulation script: `python circular_return_simulation.py`
4. Run the sensitivity chart generator: `python generate_figure7_sensitivity.py`

*Note: Running these scripts will automatically generate a new directory named `monte_carlo_outputs/` in this folder, which will contain all the summary CSV datasets and performance charts (Figures 2 to 6) discussed in the manuscript.*
